What does this program print?

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <string>

int main() {
    std::string a = "Hello";
    std::string b = "World";
    std::string c = a + ", " + b;
    std::cout << c.length() << "\n";
    return 0;
}
```

A user runs this program and types `John Smith` then presses Enter. What is printed?

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <string>

int main() {
    std::string name;
    std::cin >> name;
    std::cout << name << "\n";
    return 0;
}
```

What does this program print when the user types `cpp` and presses Enter?

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <string>

int main() {
    std::string word;
    std::cin >> word;
    std::string result = word + word;
    std::cout << result << "\n";
    std::cout << result.size() << "\n";
    return 0;
}
```

A student wants to read a full name (which may include a space) and print it. What is wrong with this code?

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <string>

int main() {
    std::string full_name;
    std::cin >> full_name;
    std::cout << "Name: " << full_name << "\n";
    return 0;
}
```

The user types `Ada Lovelace` and the student expects `Name: Ada Lovelace` to be printed.
